# Automation Lanes

Project profile: `{{ profile_name }}`

Automation lane: `{{ profile.automation_lane }}`

Human review required: `{{ profile.requires_human_review }}`

## Green

Low-risk automatic work. Auto PR dry-run is allowed. Real merge requires lane policy plus `FRONTIER_ALLOW_AUTOMERGE=1`.

## Yellow

Material engineering or research work. Claude review and CI are required before merge policy can pass. Real merge requires lane policy plus `FRONTIER_ALLOW_AUTOMERGE=1`.

## Red

External, destructive, live, production, or broker-adjacent work. Red-lane real merge remains blocked unless `FRONTIER_RED_AUTHORIZED=1`, project scope authorization matches, lane policy permits it, CI is green, and `FRONTIER_ALLOW_AUTOMERGE=1`.

Generated defaults are aggressive for local campaign execution but conservative for repository mutation: no real PR creation or automerge occurs without explicit authorization.
